</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1983" box="[905,1028,411,436]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="28" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="priapus">
<emphasis box="[905,1028,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="239">M. priapus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the only other species that have a suborbicular synsepal but not a lip with fimbriate margins.
</paragraph>
